<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,547,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,762,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamorro-Lacayo &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2004" box="[377,613,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis box="[377,613,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Polyplectropus exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified by keys, descriptions, and illustrations in the revision by Charmorro &amp; Holzenthal (2010). It is a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ross" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[773,895,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis box="[773,790,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[805,895,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group and is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ross 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Ross" baseAuthorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis box="[1318,1436,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">P. charlesi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ross, H. H." box="[159,281,835,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="35 - 126" refId="ref6632" refString="Ross, H. H. (1941) Descriptions and records of North American Trichoptera. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 67 (1084), 35 - 126, plates I - XIII." type="journal article" year="1941">Ross 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chamorro-Lacayo &amp; Holzenthal 2004" authorityName="Chamorro-Lacayo &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2004" box="[348,909,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kylistos">
<emphasis box="[348,462,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">P. kylistos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chamorro-Lacayo, M. L. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W." box="[471,909,835,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="202 - 216" refId="ref5225" refString="Chamorro-Lacayo, M. L. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W. (2004) Seven new species of Polyplectropus Ulmer (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae) from Costa Rica. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 106, 202 - 216." type="journal article" year="2004">Chamorro-Lacayo &amp; Holzenthal 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from both of these species by the absence of peg-like setae on either the dorsal or ventral branches of the inferior appendages, by the absence of endothecal phallic spines, by the acute apex of the mesoventral process of each preanal appendage, and by the presence of a narrow, lightly sclerotized process between the dorsal and ventral branches (
<bibRefCitation author="Chamorro-Lacayo, M. L. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W." pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="202 - 216" refId="ref5225" refString="Chamorro-Lacayo, M. L. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W. (2004) Seven new species of Polyplectropus Ulmer (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae) from Costa Rica. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 106, 202 - 216." type="journal article" year="2004">Chamorro-Lacayo &amp; Holzenthal 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
